TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_PROBLEM();

$a1 = random(3,9,1);
$b1 = random(2,6,1);
$e1 = ($a1+$b1)**.5;

BEGIN_TEXT
On a separate piece of paper, sketch the graph of the 
parabola \( y = x^2 + $a1 \).  On the same graph, plot 
the point \( (0, -$b1 )\).  Note that there are two 
tangent lines of \( y = x^2 + $a1 \) that pass through 
the point \( (0, -$b1 )\).
$PAR
Specifically, the tangent line of the parabola \( y = x^2 + $a1 \) at 
the point \( (a, a^2 + $a1) \) passes through the point \( (0, -$b1 )\)
where \( a > 0 \).  The other tangent line that passes through the point 
\( (0, -$b1 )\) occurs at the point \( (-a, a^2 + $a1) \).
$PAR
Find the number \( a \).
$BR
\(a\) = \{ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$ans = $e1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

END_PROBLEM();
